comment: In the Sicilian the question whether White can play Pc4 or not is vital. From the preceding examples we have seen that Black's chief trump card is his action down the half-open c-file, with the eventual central advance ... Pd5, also playing an important part If, however, White succeeds in playing Pc4, both these plans for Black are forestalled. He will not make much headway on the c-file against White's bulward at c4, while the advance ... Pd5 will be, to say the least, a difficult matter
